verbose_text: In the presence of carbidopa (BBB-impermeable), a potent AAAD inhibitor that is clinically used as a codrug together with l-Dopa (referring to Scheme XREF_FIG), the build-up of dopamine was effectively suppressed (~ 85%) even at [carbidopa] = 5 mum (0.01 equiv of l-Dopa (0.5 mm)) and completely suppressed at [carbidopa] = 50 mum (0.1 equiv).
